From: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
Date: Thu, 2 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] airoha: add forward declaration for struct sk_buff in offload header

airoha_offload.h uses struct sk_buff in function parameters but does
not forward-declare it.  When included from the mt76 driver (which
does not include linux/skbuff.h first), the compiler emits:

  error: 'struct sk_buff' declared inside parameter list will not be
  visible outside of this definition or declaration [-Werror]

Add forward declarations for struct sk_buff and struct net_device.

Signed-off-by: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>

--- a/include/linux/soc/airoha/airoha_offload.h
+++ b/include/linux/soc/airoha/airoha_offload.h
@@ -7,6 +7,9 @@
 #ifndef AIROHA_OFFLOAD_H
 #define AIROHA_OFFLOAD_H
 
+struct sk_buff;
+struct net_device;
+
 #include <linux/spinlock.h>
 #include <linux/workqueue.h>
 
